Rabat 11-16 (AFP) - A statement issued by Royal Moroccan Airlines, a copy of which was received by Agence France Presse today, Monday, said that the company decided to start two flights a week between Casablanca and Gaza as soon as the Palestinian airport is opened there.

The statement added that the company, which has scheduled these two flights for Tuesdays and Fridays, obtained permission from the Palestinian Authority and Civil Aviation.

Civil Aviation explained that the "details and required conditions will be presented to Royal Moroccan Airlines as soon as the final touches on the necessary procedures are finalized with the Israeli side."
 
Ahmad Al Bayaz, National Airport Office Director in Morocco, announced that he expects the opening of Gaza Airport in the coming days.

He added that Morocco contributed to the construction of Gaza Airport and has embarked since April 1997 on training the Palestinian personnel at the airport.
 
It is to be mentioned that about 70 Palestinians are receiving training courses in Morocco on civil aviation technologies, aircraft maintenance and meteorology.
 
In Gaza, a Moroccan delegation is waiting for the green light from the Palestinian Authority to supervise the airport's operation.